  "prompt": "Which country has the highest number of lakes?",
  "response": "The country with the highest number of lakes is **Canada**. It contains approximately **60% of the world's lakes**, with estimates ranging from **1 to 2 million lakes** depending on the definition (including even small bodies of water). Key reasons include its vast land area, glacial history, and the presence of the Canadian Shield, a region rich in freshwater ecosystems. \n\n- **Finland** is often called the \"Land of a Thousand Lakes\" but has around **187,888 lakes** (larger than 500 m\u00b2), highlighting high lake density rather than total count.  \n- **Russia** and the **United States** also have significant numbers, but Canada surpasses them due to its expansive geography and glacial legacy. \n\nThus, Canada holds the record for the most lakes globally, dwarfing other nations in sheer quantity.",
